{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"agent_message","text":"The direct executable trace answered the key question: even after the patch, the native class loader still reports “there were no resources called `reference.conf`”. So the issue is not just “missing Akka config files exist in jars”; it’s that the current metadata shape is not making them discoverable to `ClassLoader.getResources(...)`. I’m looking for a working in-repo example of Typesafe Config or similar `reference.conf` discovery under native image so I can mirror the correct pattern instead of inventing one."}}
