{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_68","type":"agent_message","text":"The image definitely contains the Akka config files, but `ClassLoader.getResources(\"reference.conf\")` still returns empty at runtime. That points to Native Image resource-discovery behavior rather than missing file inclusion. I’m looking at the local GraalVM/SubstrateVM implementation next to see what kind of resource shape `getResources()` expects for top-level entries; that should tell me whether a metadata workaround is viable."}}
