{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_143","type":"agent_message","text":"The fact that `com.typesafe:config` passes natively points away from a generic `getResources()` problem and toward Akka’s specific use of many duplicate `reference.conf` files. I’m testing the pragmatic workaround now: provide a single app-level config resource that native image can load deterministically, then see how much of the failure remains metadata-related."}}
